## Cost Optimization

### Right-Sizing

**Identify candidates**:
- Instances with <20% CPU utilization
- Memory underutilization (requires CloudWatch agent)
- Network throughput vs. instance type limits

**Actions**:
- Downsize instance types
- Use burstable instances (T3/T4g) for variable workloads
- Consider Graviton instances (ARM) for cost savings

### Reserved Instances / Savings Plans

**Strategy**:
- Purchase Reserved Instances for steady-state workloads
- Use Savings Plans for flexible commitments
- Analyze RI coverage and utilization
- Consider Convertible RIs for flexibility

**ROI**: 30-70% savings vs. on-demand pricing.

### Storage Optimization

**S3**:
- Use Intelligent-Tiering for unpredictable access patterns
- Lifecycle policies to Glacier for archives
- Delete old versions with lifecycle rules
- Enable S3 Transfer Acceleration only when needed

**EBS**:
- Use GP3 instead of GP2 (better IOPS/cost)
- Snapshot and delete unused volumes
- Enable EBS optimization for high throughput

### Spot Instances

**Use cases**:
- Batch processing
- CI/CD pipelines
- Stateless services with auto-scaling
- Machine learning training

**Savings**: 70-90% vs. on-demand pricing.

